00:30:21.488 --> 00:30:23.615
It's triggered by nightfall.

495
00:30:23.740 --> 00:30:25.183
BECCA: This is real?

496
00:30:25.283 --> 00:30:29.521
It's like somebody talking in their sleep
is how I was explained it.

497
00:30:29.621 --> 00:30:31.398
It's probably best that
we just call it a rule

498
00:30:31.498 --> 00:30:34.609
that you two shouldn't come out
of your room after 9:30 p.m.

499
00:30:34.709 --> 00:30:36.377
Deal?

500
00:30:37.253 --> 00:30:38.822
Is that a deal?

501
00:30:38.922 --> 00:30:40.673
Yeah. yeah. It's fine.

502
00:30:40.840 --> 00:30:43.201
I'm sorry about this.

503
00:30:43.301 --> 00:30:45.261
You must not be happy now.

504
00:30:45.386 --> 00:30:49.766
It's okay. Pop Pop. I'm okay.
We're just here till Saturday.

505
00:30:51.518 --> 00:30:52.769
Are you going somewhere?

506
00:30:52.894 --> 00:30:56.022
Yeah. I've got to catch the train
to go to the costume party.

507
00:30:56.189 --> 00:30:57.440
(CLEARS THROAT)

508
00:31:00.818 --> 00:31:04.013
Pop Pop. I think you're
mixing up something.

509
00:31:04.113 --> 00:31:05.281
Huh?

510
00:31:08.535 --> 00:31:10.979
Oh. man.

511
00:31:11.079 --> 00:31:12.997
Oh. man. What a...

512
00:31:13.915 --> 00:31:17.293
What a bunch of confused old fools
your grandparents turned out to be.

513
00:31:17.418 --> 00:31:19.362
That's all right. It's okay.

514
00:31:19.462 --> 00:31:20.488
(SIGHS)

515
00:31:20.588 --> 00:31:22.157
- Don't worry about it.
- Yeah.

516
00:31:22.257 --> 00:31:24.451
- Okay?
- (SNIFFS) Okay. Yeah.

517
00:31:24.551 --> 00:31:25.535
- It's okay.
- Right. Yeah.

518
00:31:25.635 --> 00:31:27.303
NANA: <i>Good morning. Cecil B. DeMille.</i>

519
00:31:28.137 --> 00:31:30.957
He was a great director.

520
00:31:31.057 --> 00:31:33.268
I made you cheddar biscuits. dear.

521
00:31:35.728 --> 00:31:39.257
Was the old coot getting ready
for the costume party again?

522
00:31:39.357 --> 00:31:41.384
BECCA: Yeah. he was.

523
00:31:41.484 --> 00:31:43.720
He's crazy.

524
00:31:43.820 --> 00:31:47.448
I'm just doing some chores in the barn.
I'll be in in a minute.

525
00:31:50.118 --> 00:31:52.328
Something happened to your computer.

526
00:31:53.580 --> 00:31:56.274
I spilled some biscuit batter on it.

527
00:31:56.374 --> 00:31:58.751
I tried to clean it with cleaner.

528
00:31:58.876 --> 00:32:00.587
I'm sorry.

529
00:32:03.339 --> 00:32:06.743
TYLER: <i>She's weird during the day.</i>
and then gets even weirder at night?

530
00:32:06.843 --> 00:32:08.703
I'm telling you it's okay.

531
00:32:08.803 --> 00:32:10.888
I downloaded the definition
of "Sundowning."

532
00:32:11.014 --> 00:32:14.250
You wouldn't understand half the words
I'm reading. The word "YOLO" isn't in it.

533
00:32:14.350 --> 00:32:17.921
It's got to do with neurological
reactions to sunshine and moonlight.

534
00:32:18.021 --> 00:32:20.523
It's literally a chemical reaction.

535
00:32:20.648 --> 00:32:24.052
"Sundown Syndrome: a term
for disorientation. agitation.

536
00:32:24.152 --> 00:32:25.845
"a general worsening of mental symptoms.

537
00:32:25.945 --> 00:32:28.932
"classically described in the elderly
at dusk or nightfall."

538
00:32:29.032 --> 00:32:32.101
It's normal old-age problems.

539
00:32:32.201 --> 00:32:34.078
People are scared
of old people for no reason.

540
00:32:34.203 --> 00:32:35.605
What about the computer?

541
00:32:35.705 --> 00:32:37.690
The only thing messed up
is the computer camera.

542
00:32:37.790 --> 00:32:39.275
There's something else going on.

543
00:32:39.375 --> 00:32:41.110
She used oven cleaner.

544
00:32:41.210 --> 00:32:44.672
and now the tiny camera
on the screen doesn't see anything.

545
00:32:44.797 --> 00:32:46.783
You don't find that odd at all?

546
00:32:46.883 --> 00:32:48.201
She made a mistake.

547
00:32:48.301 --> 00:32:51.721
Just come to accept they're old people
and things won't be as weird.

548
00:32:53.306 --> 00:32:54.415
MOM: <i>We're on the upper deck.</i>

549
00:32:54.515 --> 00:32:57.126
<i>Miguel has entered
a hairy chest competition.</i>

550
00:32:57.226 --> 00:32:58.895
<i>He's getting oiled.</i>

551
00:32:59.228 --> 00:33:00.480
(CHUCKLES)

552
00:33:01.230 --> 00:33:03.608
<i>It's so weird I can't see you.</i>

553
00:33:04.025 --> 00:33:06.135
(SIGHS) I think I can clean it off.

554
00:33:06.235 --> 00:33:08.071
<i>Tyler. why are you quiet?</i>

555
00:33:10.865 --> 00:33:13.701
Nana and Pop Pop are acting strange. Ow!

556
00:33:14.035 --> 00:33:17.455
<i>What kind of strange?
Becca. did you hit Tyler?</i>

557
00:33:17.580 --> 00:33:18.915
No.

558
00:33:19.916 --> 00:33:21.334
<i>Kids?</i>

559
00:33:24.087 --> 00:33:26.239
Pop Pop wears diapers
and he keeps them in an outhouse.

560
00:33:26.339 --> 00:33:27.824
and Nana walks around
at night without her clothes.

561
00:33:27.924 --> 00:33:30.927
and Pop Pop thinks
strangers are following him.

562
00:33:31.427 --> 00:33:35.331
(EXHALES) <i>I knew we were gonna have
this call. They're old. Tyler.</i>

563
00:33:35.431 --> 00:33:36.958
I've discussed this with him.

564
00:33:37.058 --> 00:33:39.294
<i>Old people have trouble
with their bodies sometimes.</i>

565
00:33:39.394 --> 00:33:42.839
<i>They also aren't very self-aware.
They can get paranoid. too.</i>

566
00:33:42.939 --> 00:33:44.340
<i>Becca. how strange are they acting?</i>

567
00:33:44.440 --> 00:33:46.509
They haven't been mean one second.

568
00:33:46.609 --> 00:33:49.178
- Nana crawled after us under the house.
- Playing hide-and-seek.

569
00:33:49.278 --> 00:33:51.389
<i>You guys played hide-and-seek
under the house? I used to love that!</i>

570
00:33:51.489 --> 00:33:52.515
Carrie Underwood.

571
00:33:52.615 --> 00:33:54.309
<i>T. just bear with it
for a couple of days.</i>

572
00:33:54.409 --> 00:33:57.061
<i>My parents were strange back then.
Mom was a hippie.</i>

573
00:33:57.161 --> 00:33:59.272
<i>She used to sunbathe in the back yard
without warning back then.</i>

574
00:33:59.372 --> 00:34:00.857
I'm already partially blind.

575
00:34:00.957 --> 00:34:04.527
<i>I used to get so embarrassed.
They're just weird people. honey.</i>

576
00:34:04.627 --> 00:34:06.713
<i>What level of problem is this?</i>

577
00:34:07.797 --> 00:34:08.965
One.

578
00:34:10.133 --> 00:34:11.326
One.

579
00:34:11.426 --> 00:34:12.410
See?

580
00:34:12.510 --> 00:34:14.345
<i>I miss you guys.</i>

581
00:34:14.762 --> 00:34:16.456
- (PEOPLE CHEERING OVER LAPTOP)
- Oh!

582
00:34:16.556 --> 00:34:18.708
<i>The hairy chest competition
is about to begin.</i>

583
00:34:18.808 --> 00:34:21.377
<i>I can hear the cougars clapping.</i>

584
00:34:21.477 --> 00:34:24.814
<i>I got to go. I wish I could
see your faces clearer.</i>

585
00:34:53.634 --> 00:34:55.178
Hi. honey.

586
00:34:56.846 --> 00:34:57.847
(WATER RUNNING)

587
00:35:01.809 --> 00:35:03.936
Nana. could I ask you about Mom?

588
00:35:11.778 --> 00:35:15.765
Maybe you'd be okay to talk
for a minute in an interview?

589
00:35:15.865 --> 00:35:16.866
(FAUCET CLOSED)

590
00:35:32.423 --> 00:35:36.135
Would you mind getting
inside the oven to clean it?

591
00:35:38.137 --> 00:35:39.580
I'm sorry? (SIGHS)

592
00:35:39.680 --> 00:35:43.100
I'm too big. I can't reach back there.

593
00:35:44.018 --> 00:35:46.562
The kitchen's got to be clean.

594
00:35:48.898 --> 00:35:50.566
The oven's off.

595
00:35:52.443 --> 00:35:54.904
Yeah. sure. Yeah. sure.

596
00:36:05.623 --> 00:36:07.542
Get farther in there.

597
00:36:14.924 --> 00:36:16.843
All the way in.

598
00:36:31.232 --> 00:36:34.694
Okay. I'll star in your movie.

599
00:36:38.030 --> 00:36:40.950
BECCA: If you could be any animal.
what would you be?

600
00:36:41.617 --> 00:36:43.561
Is there a right answer?

601
00:36:43.661 --> 00:36:47.123
No. these questions are intended
to get you loosened up.

602
00:36:47.331 --> 00:36:48.666
Oh.

603
00:36:51.127 --> 00:36:53.170
- A grizzly bear.
- (BOTH LAUGH)

604
00:36:54.213 --> 00:36:56.465
I think we're warm.

605
00:36:56.591 --> 00:37:00.011
Mom told me that you and Pop Pop
were very much in love.

606
00:37:00.678 --> 00:37:02.638
Where did you first meet Pop Pop?

607
00:37:03.848 --> 00:37:05.792
In a garden.

608
00:37:05.892 --> 00:37:07.919
And what did you think of him?

609
00:37:08.019 --> 00:37:10.588
Oh. he was handsome.

610
00:37:10.688 --> 00:37:14.592
He has a very strong personality.

611
00:37:14.692 --> 00:37:16.719
This is great.

612
00:37:16.819 --> 00:37:18.513
We'll come back to that.

613
00:37:18.613 --> 00:37:21.532
Right now. I want to talk
about something else.

614
00:37:21.657 --> 00:37:26.579
I know it happened a long time ago.
but what happened on the day Mom left?

615
00:37:28.247 --> 00:37:29.999
She won't tell me.

616
00:37:33.794 --> 00:37:35.546
Did she do something?

617
00:37:37.298 --> 00:37:39.383
Nana? Nana?

618
00:37:40.509 --> 00:37:42.386
(WHIMPERING)

619
00:37:42.595 --> 00:37:44.972
Nana. don't answer that question.

620
00:37:45.514 --> 00:37:47.767
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

621
00:37:51.562 --> 00:37:54.649
No more questions about Loretta Jamison.

622
00:37:55.942 --> 00:37:57.134
Maybe I can ask about...

623
00:37:57.234 --> 00:37:59.445
I don't wanna star in your movie.

624
00:38:00.404 --> 00:38:04.408
Okay. It's Wednesday night.
Three nights left.

625
00:38:05.743 --> 00:38:09.856
T-Diamond Stylus is gonna find out
what exactly is going on.

626
00:38:09.956 --> 00:38:11.707
What are you doing?

627
00:38:12.667 --> 00:38:14.360
I'm putting the camera
out tonight. Okay?

628
00:38:14.460 --> 00:38:16.070
It's like we're living with a werewolf.

629
00:38:16.170 --> 00:38:17.405
You can't record her.

630
00:38:17.505 --> 00:38:18.573
Swerve.

631
00:38:18.673 --> 00:38:21.492
I know you won't understand this because
your brain isn't fully developed yet.

632
00:38:21.592 --> 00:38:23.202
but you can't do this.

633
00:38:23.302 --> 00:38:24.720
Why?

634
00:38:25.471 --> 00:38:27.498
It's exploitative.
I have cinematic standards.

635
00:38:27.598 --> 00:38:31.043
(LAUGHING) No. No one gives a crap
about cinematic standards. okay?

636
00:38:31.143 --> 00:38:32.853
It's not the 1800s.

637
00:38:32.979 --> 00:38:34.839
Have you seen reality TV?

638
00:38:34.939 --> 00:38:38.050
<i>Housekeepers of Houston</i>
has. like. a billion viewers.

639
00:38:38.150 --> 00:38:41.262
If one of us isn't participating
in the event. we can't record it.

640
00:38:41.362 --> 00:38:42.722
It's just what's ethical.

641
00:38:42.822 --> 00:38:45.808
No offense to Ryan Seacrest or whoever
came up with the <i>Housekeepers of Houston.</i>

642
00:38:45.908 --> 00:38:49.078
You think you're so great. don't you?

643
00:38:56.961 --> 00:38:59.171
I hope things don't get weirder.

644
00:39:00.464 --> 00:39:02.299
'Cause I'm at my limit.

645
00:39:09.932 --> 00:39:11.684
TYLER: Show the clock. Show the clock.

646
00:39:14.562 --> 00:39:16.897
This is what Pop Pop was talking about.

647
00:39:18.691 --> 00:39:19.842
The werewolf is real.

648
00:39:19.942 --> 00:39:21.193
BECCA: Wait!

649
00:39:22.111 --> 00:39:24.263
She's Sundowning.

650
00:39:24.363 --> 00:39:28.868
We're participating in this.
You're not being <i>Housekeepers of Houston.</i>

651
00:39:30.828 --> 00:39:34.957
Wait. If you're gonna open the door.
just open it for a little bit.

652
00:39:54.643 --> 00:39:56.312
(CREAKING)

653
00:40:11.368 --> 00:40:12.912
- (GROWLS)
- (BECCA GASPS)

654
00:40:31.931 --> 00:40:33.082
She's supposed to do that?

655
00:40:33.182 --> 00:40:35.626
BECCA: It's just like someone
talking in their sleep.

656
00:40:35.726 --> 00:40:37.895
You used to talk in your sleep
till you were seven.

657
00:40:38.020 --> 00:40:40.856
Dad used to come in and quiet you down.

658
00:41:05.756 --> 00:41:07.174
Hey. Becca.

659
00:41:08.926 --> 00:41:10.219
Who am I?

660
00:41:17.143 --> 00:41:19.728
BECCA: T. T.

661
00:41:24.900 --> 00:41:28.971
There's a family of foxes.
You're going to miss it.

662
00:41:29.071 --> 00:41:30.739
- We're coming!
- BECCA: We're coming!

663
00:41:34.577 --> 00:41:36.036
BECCA: Just stop.

664
00:41:44.211 --> 00:41:45.946
TYLER: Why is Nana
staring into the well?

665
00:41:46.046 --> 00:41:49.033
Come on. let's go.
Come on. enough of that.

666
00:41:49.133 --> 00:41:50.634
- BECCA: I don't know.
- POP POP: Come on.

667
00:41:59.101 --> 00:42:01.170
<i>Mise-en-scène.</i>

668
00:42:01.270 --> 00:42:04.757
BECCA: You know. you're not
as dumb as your performance

669
00:42:04.857 --> 00:42:06.175
on standardized tests would indicate.

670
00:42:06.275 --> 00:42:07.735
Oh. Oh!

671
00:42:08.402 --> 00:42:10.446
I forgot I had something for you.

672
00:42:16.327 --> 00:42:21.332
When you think of Dad now.
in California. do you still like him?

673
00:42:22.499 --> 00:42:24.985
I don't know. Stuff happens.

674
00:42:25.085 --> 00:42:27.696
No. but Dad is hilarious. Dad's funny.

675
00:42:27.796 --> 00:42:31.075
He sent the funny card of the fat lady
on the boardwalk. (LAUGHS)

676
00:42:31.175 --> 00:42:32.910
Do you remember that?

677
00:42:33.010 --> 00:42:35.137
What do you mean "stuff happens"?

678
00:42:37.640 --> 00:42:39.183
People leave.

679
00:42:40.142 --> 00:42:43.629
Because they find something
they like better.

680
00:42:43.729 --> 00:42:45.898
So you don't feel bad?

681
00:42:47.066 --> 00:42:48.442
No.

682
00:42:50.110 --> 00:42:52.321
You're not being truthful.

683
00:42:53.155 --> 00:42:56.992
Well. you can believe what you want.
but this is how I feel.

684
00:42:58.118 --> 00:42:59.912
Make me believe you.

685
00:43:05.209 --> 00:43:09.446
So. I'm on the Titans pee wee
football team and it was third down.

686
00:43:09.546 --> 00:43:12.283
It was at the end and we were leading.

687
00:43:12.383 --> 00:43:14.343
So if we stop them.
we probably win the game.

688
00:43:14.510 --> 00:43:17.121
Give me context. How old are you?

689
00:43:17.221 --> 00:43:18.973
I'm eight.

690
00:43:20.307 --> 00:43:22.643
So. I'm free safety.

691
00:43:22.810 --> 00:43:24.920
Which means that I'm supposed
to tackle the guy

692
00:43:25.020 --> 00:43:28.274
if he makes it past
the people on the line.

693
00:43:28.399 --> 00:43:29.925
- So. their running back punches the hole...
- Okay.

694
00:43:30.025 --> 00:43:32.069
Am I supposed to be
following these terms?

695
00:43:32.194 --> 00:43:34.405
Are these phrases supposed
to mean something to me?

696
00:43:34.530 --> 00:43:35.948
Just listen.

697
00:43:37.533 --> 00:43:40.869
So their running back. who's big.
makes it past the line.

698
00:43:40.995 --> 00:43:43.606
and I'm the only one left to tackle him.

699
00:43:43.706 --> 00:43:44.732
All I got to do is tackle him.

700
00:43:44.832 --> 00:43:47.251
put my hands around him
and tackle him. but...

701
00:43:49.878 --> 00:43:51.547
I just stand there.

702
00:43:52.881 --> 00:43:56.285
They call it "freezing"
and I could hear everyone yelling.

703
00:43:56.385 --> 00:44:00.347
Coach Daugherty. Dad.
All my teammates. and...

704
00:44:01.557 --> 00:44:03.500
He gets the first down
and runs and runs.

705
00:44:03.600 --> 00:44:07.563
and the other team is celebrating.
and I'm still standing there.

706
00:44:11.400 --> 00:44:12.735
Same place.

707
00:44:15.446 --> 00:44:18.265
Then the assistant coach
came and got me.

708
00:44:18.365 --> 00:44:20.476
and Dad patted me on the shoulder
and then went to the car.

709
00:44:20.576 --> 00:44:24.246
and he never told me
he was angry or anything.

710
00:44:26.582 --> 00:44:28.692
You think Dad didn't
say anything and left

711
00:44:28.792 --> 00:44:31.587
because you didn't tackle
another eight-year-old in a game

712
00:44:31.754 --> 00:44:33.380
five years ago?

713
00:44:38.052 --> 00:44:40.763
When you say it like that.
it sounds stupid.

714
00:44:42.222 --> 00:44:44.266
(CLANKING)

715
00:44:46.727 --> 00:44:48.337
BECCA: Why are we here?

716
00:44:48.437 --> 00:44:50.272
TYLER: She was staring at something.

717
00:44:59.448 --> 00:45:01.950
So. what did you find?

718
00:45:04.244 --> 00:45:05.412
It's only water.

719
00:45:10.918 --> 00:45:13.253
So. I just read these in order?

720
00:45:16.590 --> 00:45:18.534
"If you could be any animal.
what would it be?"

721
00:45:18.634 --> 00:45:21.136
- I feel like a douche. Becca.
- Shut up.

722
00:45:21.970 --> 00:45:23.372
I would be a dolphin.

723
00:45:23.472 --> 00:45:25.499
It's an intuitive and highly
intelligent creature

724
00:45:25.599 --> 00:45:28.477
with great power
and poetry in its movements.

725
00:45:29.311 --> 00:45:34.149
How come you like the pizza delivery guy.
even though he has all that ratchet acne?

726
00:45:38.320 --> 00:45:40.030
Please answer the question.

727
00:45:44.952 --> 00:45:46.328
He's kind.

728
00:45:47.704 --> 00:45:49.331
He has kind eyes.

729
00:45:52.835 --> 00:45:56.296
How come you don't look
at yourself in the mirror?

730
00:45:56.839 --> 00:46:00.242
Okay. fine. What's this now?

731
00:46:00.342 --> 00:46:03.787
Besides when you're editing.
you don't like looking at yourself.

732
00:46:03.887 --> 00:46:05.164
You never look at
yourself in the mirror.

733
00:46:05.264 --> 00:46:07.958
You comb your hair
with your back to the mirror.

734
00:46:08.058 --> 00:46:10.461
And I see you brush your teeth.

735
00:46:10.561 --> 00:46:12.938
You look down the whole time.

736
00:46:16.650 --> 00:46:19.570
Your sweater's inside out.
Did you know that?

737
00:46:21.196 --> 00:46:23.574
Did you see that in
the mirror this morning?

738
00:46:24.867 --> 00:46:26.535
Is that correct?

739
00:46:31.540 --> 00:46:34.209
It doesn't feel so good. does it?

740
00:46:36.211 --> 00:46:39.715
Are you changing
the focal length of the lens?

741
00:46:39.840 --> 00:46:41.717
No. I don't even know what that is.

742
00:46:41.842 --> 00:46:43.677
Are you zooming?

743
00:46:44.511 --> 00:46:45.762
No.

744
00:46:49.892 --> 00:46:52.753
So do you admit that
you don't look at yourself.

745
00:46:52.853 --> 00:46:55.297
or are you gonna keep lying?

746
00:46:55.397 --> 00:46:57.900
When do you think I started doing that?

747
00:46:58.609 --> 00:47:00.152
You know when.

748
00:47:02.237 --> 00:47:05.282
That's not true. asshole.

749
00:47:05.407 --> 00:47:07.743
You think you're worthless.

750
00:47:08.202 --> 00:47:09.578
Admit it.

751
00:47:13.665 --> 00:47:15.501
(SOBBING)

752
00:47:18.462 --> 00:47:20.923
He gave me a card when he left.

753
00:47:24.051 --> 00:47:25.594
A card.

754
00:47:31.433 --> 00:47:33.602
Old footage of us as kids.

755
00:47:34.978 --> 00:47:37.314
I was thinking of using it in the doc.

756
00:47:38.815 --> 00:47:41.735
I refuse to use anything
that has my dad in it.

757
00:47:43.445 --> 00:47:45.155
That would mean I forgive him.

758
00:47:54.248 --> 00:47:55.457
TYLER: Nana?

759
00:48:00.087 --> 00:48:01.296
Nana?

760
00:48:07.636 --> 00:48:09.179
Becca's blind.

761
00:48:11.265 --> 00:48:13.417
I know I'm right.

762
00:48:13.517 --> 00:48:15.894
That there is something going on here.

763
00:48:19.147 --> 00:48:22.426
Maybe there's something
down in the basement.

764
00:48:22.526 --> 00:48:26.263
They don't want us to go down there.
They're throwing shade.

765
00:48:26.363 --> 00:48:27.931
Speak English.

766
00:48:28.031 --> 00:48:30.492
They could be hiding
something down there.

767
00:48:30.617 --> 00:48:33.562
There's mold down there.
That's why they don't want us to go down.

768
00:48:33.662 --> 00:48:35.731
Just stop. okay?

769
00:48:35.831 --> 00:48:38.500
Just let me put the camera out.

770
00:48:42.879 --> 00:48:46.575
Hi. I'm Stacey.
Is Mr. and Mrs. Jamison around?

771
00:48:46.675 --> 00:48:49.928
BECCA: No. they just stepped out.
It's just me and my brother here.

772
00:48:51.513 --> 00:48:54.474
Mr. and Mrs. Jamison were
counselors at Meadowbrook.

773
00:48:54.641 --> 00:48:57.211
I was in the rehab program there.

774
00:48:57.311 --> 00:49:00.631
They used to sit by my bed
when I wasn't in good shape.

775
00:49:00.731 --> 00:49:03.217
All night sometimes.

776
00:49:03.317 --> 00:49:06.194
Anyway. this is
a blueberry cobbler for them.

777
00:49:06.320 --> 00:49:09.531
They were supposed to stop by
on Saturday but they never showed.

778
00:49:09.656 --> 00:49:11.934
I know Mrs. Jamison
hadn't been feeling herself.

779
00:49:12.034 --> 00:49:15.437
so I thought I'd just stop by
and check in on them.

780
00:49:15.537 --> 00:49:18.273
They hear all that scuttlebutt
down at Maple Shade?

781
00:49:18.373 --> 00:49:20.375
Uh. I don't think so.

782
00:49:22.169 --> 00:49:24.321
Stacey. it's okay. Just be natural.

783
00:49:24.421 --> 00:49:26.715
I'm just getting portraits of everybody.

784
00:49:27.924 --> 00:49:29.551
Just be natural.

785
00:49:30.594 --> 00:49:32.554
Uh. okay. never mind.

786
00:49:54.701 --> 00:49:55.911
Pop Pop?

787
00:50:13.720 --> 00:50:14.930
Pop Pop?

788
00:50:17.432 --> 00:50:18.500
- (SCREAMS)
- (GASPS)

789
00:50:18.600 --> 00:50:20.043
(SIGHS)

790
00:50:20.143 --> 00:50:21.645
We're even.

791
00:50:24.106 --> 00:50:25.399
(BECCA CHUCKLES)

792
00:50:25.649 --> 00:50:27.426
I've been editing montages with music.

793
00:50:27.526 --> 00:50:29.344
but I need some everyday footage
of our grandparents.

794
00:50:29.444 --> 00:50:32.306
so I've decided to spend Thursday
afternoon following them around.

795
00:50:32.406 --> 00:50:33.849
(NANA LAUGHING)

796
00:50:33.949 --> 00:50:37.019
Hear that? She's laughing
as she's watching TV.

797
00:50:37.119 --> 00:50:39.746
Maybe Mom and her watch the same shows.

798
00:50:40.288 --> 00:50:42.524
(MUSIC PLAYING OVER TV)

799
00:50:42.624 --> 00:50:44.334
(CHAIR CREAKING)

800
00:50:46.044 --> 00:50:47.921
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

801
00:51:01.768 --> 00:51:03.545
BECCA: Nana?

802
00:51:03.645 --> 00:51:05.313
Nana. are you okay?

803
00:51:07.482 --> 00:51:09.317
Good afternoon.

804
00:51:10.152 --> 00:51:11.987
I heard you laughing.

805
00:51:13.113 --> 00:51:15.991
I have the deep darkies.

806
00:51:25.375 --> 00:51:26.918
Nana? Nana!

807
00:51:27.043 --> 00:51:29.963
Nana. Nana. Nana. stop! Nana. stop!

808
00:51:36.136 --> 00:51:38.413
Nana. what's happening?

809
00:51:38.513 --> 00:51:43.852
You have to laugh to keep
the deep darkies in a cave.

810
00:51:47.564 --> 00:51:49.566
(BECCA BREATHING HEAVILY)

811
00:51:52.736 --> 00:51:54.196
Pop Pop?

812
00:52:00.202 --> 00:52:01.411
Pop Pop. I think Nana's...

813
00:52:01.536 --> 00:52:02.854
I was just cleaning it.

814
00:52:02.954 --> 00:52:04.606
What is that?

815
00:52:04.706 --> 00:52:07.375
You want something?

816
00:52:07.542 --> 00:52:10.278
I was just cleaning it. really.

817
00:52:10.378 --> 00:52:13.507
I think Nana's not feeling well.

818
00:52:17.552 --> 00:52:20.055
Thank you. Becca. I'll check on her.

819
00:52:23.642 --> 00:52:25.352
(BECCA BREATHES HEAVILY)

820
00:52:26.019 --> 00:52:27.687
BECCA:
<i>We're putting the camera out tonight.</i>

821
00:52:38.573 --> 00:52:40.242
(WHISPERS) What do you think?

822
00:52:53.922 --> 00:52:55.407
<i>Whoo-hoo! Ladies!</i>

823
00:52:55.507 --> 00:52:57.659
MIGUEL: <i>That's right. I'm bad. I'm bad.</i>

824
00:52:57.759 --> 00:53:00.762
She seems like she's better off
without us.

825
00:53:00.929 --> 00:53:03.098
We're doing this
so Mom can have a life. dummy.

826
00:53:04.850 --> 00:53:07.085
MALE HIP-HOP INSTRUCTOR: <i>Give me
some real Doug E. Fresh now. people.</i>

827
00:53:07.185 --> 00:53:08.854
<i>From the top. Here we go.</i>

828
00:53:11.106 --> 00:53:12.482
Good night!

829
00:53:12.607 --> 00:53:14.317
Is everything okay?

830
00:53:14.442 --> 00:53:15.677
BECCA: We're fine.

831
00:53:15.777 --> 00:53:17.679
You sure?

832
00:53:17.779 --> 00:53:20.182
You both seem to be acting funny.

833
00:53:20.282 --> 00:53:23.118
We're terrific. just terrific.
Thanks for asking.

834
00:53:23.243 --> 00:53:24.770
- Okay.
- BECCA: Good night.

835
00:53:24.870 --> 00:53:27.289
Good night. Good night.

836
00:53:37.966 --> 00:53:39.301
- What am I gonna do?
- What happened?

837
00:53:39.426 --> 00:53:41.536
There aren't any tissues
left in the bathroom

838
00:53:41.636 --> 00:53:42.846
and I had to touch the toilet handle.

839
00:53:42.971 --> 00:53:45.098
- There's something on my hand though.
- Okay. Let me see.

840
00:53:45.223 --> 00:53:47.375
- You can't see it but I can feel it!
- (SHUSHING)

841
00:53:47.475 --> 00:53:50.045
- Tyler. Tyler.
- It's disgusting. Nothing's...

842
00:53:50.145 --> 00:53:51.797
- Nothing's coming off!
- Let me have a look.

843
00:53:51.897 --> 00:53:54.883
I can feel it.
There's no tissues left. Becca.

844
00:53:54.983 --> 00:53:57.052
Tyler. there are tissues
underneath the sink.

845
00:53:57.152 --> 00:53:58.637
- Where? What?
- It's okay.

846
00:53:58.737 --> 00:54:00.013
It's too late.

847
00:54:00.113 --> 00:54:02.032
- No. it's not gonna come off.
- I think it is.

848
00:54:02.157 --> 00:54:04.534
- Rubbing it isn't gonna make it come off!
- (SHUSHING)

849
00:54:04.659 --> 00:54:07.162
It's okay. It's all right.

850
00:54:07.287 --> 00:54:08.438
I can feel it though.

851
00:54:08.538 --> 00:54:10.498
I'm definitely getting at it. Look.

852
00:54:12.792 --> 00:54:14.836
It's definitely coming off.

853
00:54:15.795 --> 00:54:17.422
- You sure?
- There.

854
00:54:20.008 --> 00:54:21.034
See?

855
00:54:21.134 --> 00:54:22.327
Yeah.

856
00:54:22.427 --> 00:54:23.970
Just look next time. all right?

857
00:54:24.095 --> 00:54:25.972
- I didn't know they were there.
- It's okay.

858
00:54:28.224 --> 00:54:29.517
(SIGHS)

859
00:55:29.828 --> 00:55:31.871
(APPROACHING FOOTSTEPS)

860
00:55:33.540 --> 00:55:34.916
(ROARS)

861
00:55:42.841 --> 00:55:45.010
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

862
00:56:31.639 --> 00:56:32.791
(BANGING SOUND)

863
00:56:32.891 --> 00:56:34.100
TYLER: Becca?

864
00:56:44.819 --> 00:56:46.738
BECCA: (WHISPERS) Stay in bed.

865
00:56:53.620 --> 00:56:54.746
(LOUD BANG)

866
00:57:26.653 --> 00:57:27.862
(SIGHS)

867
00:57:29.531 --> 00:57:32.392
Mom will be home late this afternoon.

868
00:57:32.492 --> 00:57:34.978
We're ending this trip tonight.

869
00:57:35.078 --> 00:57:37.622
We stay away from them unless I say.

870
00:57:39.374 --> 00:57:40.917
Pack your bags.

871
00:57:46.589 --> 00:57:50.385
I still need them to
give Mom the elixir.

872
00:57:50.510 --> 00:57:52.762
TYLER: Becca. what's the elixir?

873
00:57:56.891 --> 00:57:58.726
BECCA: Just pretend like you're playing.

874
00:57:59.811 --> 00:58:01.796
Is everything all right?

875
00:58:01.896 --> 00:58:03.648
We're just playing.

876
00:58:09.070 --> 00:58:10.680
Uh. do you wanna do the interview?

877
00:58:10.780 --> 00:58:12.724
TYLER: What? What are you doing?

878
00:58:12.824 --> 00:58:17.245
I thought we were staying away from them.
Becca. You're gonna interview him?

879
00:58:24.752 --> 00:58:28.423
Mom told me you worked
in the coal industry for a long time.

880
00:58:29.632 --> 00:58:31.701
I did work in a factory.

881
00:58:31.801 --> 00:58:33.536
I know.

882
00:58:33.636 --> 00:58:35.430
Worked at night.

883
00:58:36.264 --> 00:58:38.766
Saw a white thing running around.

884
00:58:40.143 --> 00:58:41.252
A white thing?

885
00:58:41.352 --> 00:58:43.771
Yeah. it used to run around
the factory at night.

886
00:58:45.607 --> 00:58:47.842
Only I saw it.

887
00:58:47.942 --> 00:58:52.113
I started to tell people about it
and they didn't believe me.

888
00:58:53.323 --> 00:58:55.116
Had yellow eyes.

889
00:58:57.785 --> 00:58:59.787
Then they fired me.

890
00:59:01.414 --> 00:59:03.499
And nobody talked to me.

891
00:59:07.670 --> 00:59:09.464
Mom didn't tell me that.

892
00:59:09.631 --> 00:59:13.134
Oh. she doesn't know.
Happened after she left.

893
00:59:17.680 --> 00:59:19.641
Pop Pop. you seem down.

894
00:59:21.309 --> 00:59:22.810
Well. it's just. uh...

895
00:59:24.771 --> 00:59:26.856
The end of your trip.

896
00:59:29.442 --> 00:59:31.861
I know it's all coming to an end.

897
00:59:34.822 --> 00:59:37.742
Why don't you just ask
Mom if you can visit?

898
00:59:38.952 --> 00:59:41.079
Are you really still angry?

899
00:59:43.164 --> 00:59:44.332
(SIGHS)

900
00:59:48.044 --> 00:59:51.506
She can't get over this.
She still thinks you're mad at her.

901
00:59:59.806 --> 01:00:02.850
TYLER: That whole "white thing" story.
the hairs on my arm stood up.

902
01:00:02.976 --> 01:00:05.587
It's definitely some sort of
late onset schizophrenia.

903
01:00:05.687 --> 01:00:07.897
They're both in bad shape.

904
01:00:08.022 --> 01:00:10.258
Great. Our Pop Pop has schizophrenia.

905
01:00:10.358 --> 01:00:13.903
and our Nana becomes Michael Myers
when the sun goes down.

906
01:00:20.910 --> 01:00:21.978
BECCA: That's Stacey.

907
01:00:22.078 --> 01:00:24.414
...ride in my car.

908
01:00:24.539 --> 01:00:27.233
Okay. stop. What did you do...

909
01:00:27.333 --> 01:00:29.335
TYLER: What? Why is she angry?

910
01:00:30.586 --> 01:00:34.090
She must be telling them
that they need to get help.

911
01:00:34.215 --> 01:00:35.575
I don't...

912
01:00:35.675 --> 01:00:36.993
Just come to the back here.

913
01:00:37.093 --> 01:00:38.720
I don't want you to touch me.

914
01:00:39.887 --> 01:00:41.389
Come to the back.

915
01:00:42.724 --> 01:00:43.933
Okay.

916
01:00:46.269 --> 01:00:47.979
I got it all off.

917
01:00:48.104 --> 01:00:50.606
TYLER: I didn't see Stacey leave.

918
01:00:50.732 --> 01:00:52.066
Did you?

919
01:00:55.903 --> 01:00:57.947
Nana said okay.

920
01:01:01.075 --> 01:01:04.912
BECCA: Thanks for doing this.
We're leaving soon. Nana.

921
01:01:05.038 --> 01:01:07.273
I'm sad it's all over.

922
01:01:07.373 --> 01:01:10.151
This is the last time
I'll get to ask you questions.

923
01:01:10.251 --> 01:01:14.130
It's like the big end to my film.
and like you said. you're the star.

924
01:01:14.380 --> 01:01:15.965
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

925
01:01:16.758 --> 01:01:19.744
Tell me anything.
Whatever you want to talk about.

926
01:01:19.844 --> 01:01:23.665
I know a story. It's about water.

927
01:01:23.765 --> 01:01:24.891
Great.

928
01:01:26.392 --> 01:01:31.481
There is a pond that has
little creatures in it.

929
01:01:31.606 --> 01:01:36.235
These creatures are from another planet
but no one realizes it.

930
01:01:37.236 --> 01:01:41.616
These creatures spit
into the water all day long.

931
01:01:42.575 --> 01:01:46.454
Their spit can make
you sleep. but not die.

932
01:01:47.622 --> 01:01:51.109
When people go underwater in the pond.

933
01:01:51.209 --> 01:01:54.462
they go into a deep sleep.

934
01:01:54.587 --> 01:01:57.131
A really beautiful sleep.

935
01:01:58.424 --> 01:02:00.118
The creatures from another planet have

936
01:02:00.218 --> 01:02:03.262
many people at the bottom of the pond.

937
01:02:03.888 --> 01:02:06.374
storing them up.

938
01:02:06.474 --> 01:02:08.209
They are going to take them back

939
01:02:08.309 --> 01:02:11.562
to their planet of
Sinmorfitellia one day.

940
01:02:16.651 --> 01:02:18.386
That's just a made-up story.

941
01:02:18.486 --> 01:02:20.305
It's not real.

942
01:02:20.405 --> 01:02:22.515
Wow. that's some story.

943
01:02:22.615 --> 01:02:24.559
And the creatures have antennas.

944
01:02:24.659 --> 01:02:27.437
but they are invisible antennas.

945
01:02:27.537 --> 01:02:28.871
(CHUCKLES)

946
01:02:32.291 --> 01:02:33.960
Can we talk about Mom?

947
01:02:38.840 --> 01:02:40.800
You don't ever want to see her?

948
01:02:44.178 --> 01:02:46.139
No.

949
01:02:46.264 --> 01:02:48.082
Never.

950
01:02:48.182 --> 01:02:52.812
On the day she left.
she must have done something.

951
01:02:55.773 --> 01:02:56.899
(SOBS)

952
01:02:57.692 --> 01:02:59.026
Okay. okay.

953
01:02:59.152 --> 01:03:01.988
Let's pretend we're
telling another story.

954
01:03:02.697 --> 01:03:06.434
And the story concerns a young girl

955
01:03:06.534 --> 01:03:09.245
who thinks she's in love
with an older man.

956
01:03:09.704 --> 01:03:12.165
and they decide to run off together.

957
01:03:18.171 --> 01:03:21.532
Now. the parents of the girl
warn her that this won't work.

958
01:03:21.632 --> 01:03:23.885
And they refuse to let her go.

959
01:03:25.344 --> 01:03:27.455
And then one day.
the girl gets into a horrible fight

960
01:03:27.555 --> 01:03:29.348
with them and leaves forever.

961
01:03:29.640 --> 01:03:30.708
(NANA SNIFFLES)

962
01:03:30.808 --> 01:03:33.686
Now. the parents in
this story don't know it.

963
01:03:34.729 --> 01:03:37.465
but she misses them a lot.

964
01:03:37.565 --> 01:03:40.443
And she suffers greatly.

965
01:03:42.487 --> 01:03:44.947
And then the worst thing happens.

966
01:03:46.741 --> 01:03:51.204
The man. he breaks the girl's heart
and leaves forever.

967
01:03:53.039 --> 01:03:55.958
And leave their two
small children behind.

968
01:03:57.293 --> 01:03:59.362
(SNIFFLES) So. Nana.

969
01:03:59.462 --> 01:04:03.591
Nana. in this story.
what do you hope will happen to the girl?

970
01:04:06.302 --> 01:04:10.081
In this story. is she very sad?

971
01:04:10.181 --> 01:04:13.459
She's inconsolable at times.
She tries everything to be happy.

972
01:04:13.559 --> 01:04:16.671
Medications and goes
to therapy for four years

973
01:04:16.771 --> 01:04:18.172
but still remains a little sad.

974
01:04:18.272 --> 01:04:20.174
I don't like this story.

975
01:04:20.274 --> 01:04:21.467
Nana. what do you think

976
01:04:21.567 --> 01:04:25.154
the parents in this story
should do if they saw the girl again?

977
01:04:27.990 --> 01:04:30.351
Nana. pretend you were in this story

978
01:04:30.451 --> 01:04:33.271
and she was your daughter. and she left.

979
01:04:33.371 --> 01:04:36.749
What would you say
when you finally saw her again?

980
01:04:40.336 --> 01:04:42.296
I would tell her.

981
01:04:45.299 --> 01:04:48.135
"I forgive you. little girl."

982
01:04:53.057 --> 01:04:54.725
(SNIFFLES)

983
01:04:55.017 --> 01:04:56.561
(SOBBING)

984
01:05:07.405 --> 01:05:10.408
NANA: (OVER VIDEO)
<i>"I forgive you. little girl."</i>

985
01:05:12.660 --> 01:05:14.495
BECCA: That's the elixir.

986
01:05:24.422 --> 01:05:26.574
What are you doing?

987
01:05:26.674 --> 01:05:29.135
This is how children play. okay?

988
01:05:42.315 --> 01:05:44.175
Hey. Mom should be home.

989
01:05:44.275 --> 01:05:45.760
Let's go and Skype with her
while they're in the back.

990
01:05:45.860 --> 01:05:47.028
Right.

991
01:05:49.655 --> 01:05:51.532
This will be the denouement.

992
01:05:53.367 --> 01:05:55.870
(DIAL TONE RINGING)

993
01:05:59.332 --> 01:06:00.374
MOM: <i>Hey. kiddos!</i>

994
01:06:00.499 --> 01:06:03.669
<i>Did you get my videos?
I know. I look like an apple.</i>

995
01:06:04.211 --> 01:06:05.947
<i>Trip was great.</i>

996
01:06:06.047 --> 01:06:07.715
<i>Miguel and I had a little fight
this morning.</i>

997
01:06:07.840 --> 01:06:11.285
<i>He wanted to get short stack pancakes.
I told him he was gaining a little weight.</i>

998
01:06:11.385 --> 01:06:13.471
<i>Can you believe it?
Things don't work out for me.</i>

999
01:06:13.888 --> 01:06:15.122
- Mom?
- <i>Yeah?</i>

1000
01:06:15.222 --> 01:06:17.224
Mom. you need to come
and get us right now.

1001
01:06:18.893 --> 01:06:19.961
<i>What? What happened?</i>

1002
01:06:20.061 --> 01:06:22.797
Mom. get in the car and come right now.

1003
01:06:22.897 --> 01:06:25.383
<i>Do you know how long
that would take by car. Rebecca?</i>

1004
01:06:25.483 --> 01:06:28.469
(SIGHS) Mom. trust me. there is
something wrong with Nana and Pop Pop.

1005
01:06:28.569 --> 01:06:30.972
I'm telling you. you need to come
and pick us up tonight.

1006
01:06:31.072 --> 01:06:34.475
<i>Becca. you're scaring me.
My heart is in my throat.</i>

1007
01:06:34.575 --> 01:06:36.702
We're okay now. Just come.

1008
01:06:37.828 --> 01:06:39.814
<i>Where are they now?</i>

1009
01:06:39.914 --> 01:06:43.192
Uh. they're outside
by the chicken coops.

1010
01:06:43.292 --> 01:06:44.919
They won't see you.

1011
01:06:56.222 --> 01:06:57.206
<i>Becca...</i>

1012
01:06:57.306 --> 01:07:00.334
BECCA: They've been acting so strange.
Mom. We've been recording them.

1013
01:07:00.434 --> 01:07:01.502
<i>Becca...</i>

1014
01:07:01.602 --> 01:07:05.314
Yeah. I kept telling Becca
something was wrong. didn't I?

1015
01:07:05.648 --> 01:07:06.674
<i>Becca. Tyler...</i>

1016
01:07:06.774 --> 01:07:09.485
And Nana walks around
at night with a knife.

1017
01:07:09.610 --> 01:07:11.762
- And Pop Pop had a gun in his mouth.
- <i>Rebecca. Tyler...</i>

1018
01:07:11.862 --> 01:07:14.532
I think he was trying to hurt himself.

1019
01:07:14.907 --> 01:07:19.704
<i>Becca. Tyler. babies. I need you
to listen to me very carefully.</i>

1020
01:07:19.829 --> 01:07:22.623
<i>Becca. Tyler. just listen to me.</i>

1021
01:07:23.624 --> 01:07:24.959
We are.

1022
01:07:27.128 --> 01:07:29.463
<i>Those aren't your grandparents.</i>

1023
01:07:32.341 --> 01:07:34.802
What are you talking about. Mom?

1024
01:07:37.430 --> 01:07:39.807
<i>Where are Nana and Pop Pop?</i>

1025
01:07:41.976 --> 01:07:45.146
<i>You've been staying
with those people the whole time?</i>

1026
01:07:50.192 --> 01:07:51.861
(SHUDDERING EXHALE)

1027
01:07:53.821 --> 01:07:55.948
<i>Masonville Police Department.</i>

1028
01:07:56.657 --> 01:07:58.367
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

1029
01:07:59.452 --> 01:08:00.995
(SIGHS) <i>Come on. come on.</i>

1030
01:08:04.248 --> 01:08:05.499
(GASPS)

1031
01:08:07.710 --> 01:08:09.612
What are you guys doing?

1032
01:08:09.712 --> 01:08:11.505
We'll be right in. sweethearts.

1033
01:08:12.798 --> 01:08:14.742
VOICEMAIL: <i>This is the Masonville
County Police Department.</i>

1034
01:08:14.842 --> 01:08:17.495
<i>Our officer. Jerry.
is currently out on dispatch.</i>

1035
01:08:17.595 --> 01:08:19.180
<i>Please leave a message...</i>

1036
01:08:19.346 --> 01:08:23.184
<i>Police aren't answering.
Damn it! Stupid hick town.</i>

1037
01:08:23.309 --> 01:08:26.979
<i>Okay. I'm gonna keep calling
from the car. I promise.</i>

1038
01:08:27.104 --> 01:08:28.673
- <i>Get you and your brother out.</i>
- (WHISPERS) Okay.

1039
01:08:28.773 --> 01:08:29.965
<i>Try to get to a neighbor.</i>

1040
01:08:30.065 --> 01:08:31.942
- Just stay calm. T.
- <i>I'm coming.</i>

1041
01:08:32.067 --> 01:08:33.861
- (WHISPERS) We're in a house with...
- (DOOR OPENS)

1042
01:08:37.198 --> 01:08:40.409
After we clear up.
I have a fantastic idea.

1043
01:08:40.534 --> 01:08:44.313
We should play a board game!
Families play board games.

1044
01:08:44.413 --> 01:08:45.981
It's our last night together.

1045
01:08:46.081 --> 01:08:47.108
NANA: Becca?

1046
01:08:47.208 --> 01:08:49.235
You'll help me clean up. right?

1047
01:08:49.335 --> 01:08:51.587
You can record it with your camera.

1048
01:08:56.759 --> 01:08:57.827
BECCA: Okay.

1049
01:08:57.927 --> 01:08:59.203
Yeah! (LAUGHS)

1050
01:08:59.303 --> 01:09:00.346
(SNIFFS)

1051
01:09:22.743 --> 01:09:25.996
Maybe we should go outside and film
some evening shots of the house.

1052
01:09:27.623 --> 01:09:29.917
Okay. sounds good. sister.

1053
01:09:30.584 --> 01:09:33.128
Could you clean the oven for me. Becca?

1054
01:09:48.060 --> 01:09:49.044
(CHUCKLES)

1055
01:09:49.144 --> 01:09:51.105
Get all the way inside.

1056
01:09:51.397 --> 01:09:52.982
TYLER: Mmm. Becca?

1057
01:09:53.107 --> 01:09:54.441
She's done it before.

1058
01:09:54.984 --> 01:09:57.695
We really should film something outside.

1059
01:09:58.487 --> 01:10:00.514
Do this first.

1060
01:10:00.614 --> 01:10:02.449
I'll be quick.

1061
01:10:06.704 --> 01:10:08.789
Oh. this will just
take a second. (GRUNTS)

1062
01:10:09.123 --> 01:10:11.458
BECCA: (MUFFLED) Nana? Nana?

1063
01:10:12.793 --> 01:10:13.944
I can clean those.

1064
01:10:14.044 --> 01:10:15.446
BECCA: Nana. please open the door.

1065
01:10:15.546 --> 01:10:16.881
NANA: Oh. that's okay.

1066
01:10:17.840 --> 01:10:18.908
Please open it.

1067
01:10:19.008 --> 01:10:20.509
There she is.

1068
01:10:23.387 --> 01:10:25.431
So. what was the big fuss?

1069
01:10:31.186 --> 01:10:32.713
Let's make it...

1070
01:10:32.813 --> 01:10:33.839
(DICE RATTLING)

1071
01:10:33.939 --> 01:10:35.983
...a perfect family night.

1072
01:10:36.108 --> 01:10:37.985
(CHUCKLES)

1073
01:10:38.611 --> 01:10:39.653
Oh!

1074
01:10:42.823 --> 01:10:44.700
(LAUGHS)

1075
01:10:49.413 --> 01:10:52.750
Your Pop Pop is very competitive
with board games.

1076
01:10:52.875 --> 01:10:54.501
Be warned.

1077
01:10:55.419 --> 01:10:57.238
POP POP: If you want to move
that over here. that's fine.

1078
01:10:57.338 --> 01:10:59.365
NANA: If we use this table.
there's not room for the cookies.

1079
01:10:59.465 --> 01:11:03.035
T-Diamond Stylus and I are gonna do one
last interview outside and be right back.

1080
01:11:03.135 --> 01:11:04.345
NANA: You can sit over there.

1081
01:11:04.470 --> 01:11:06.263
Figure out what the teams are.

1082
01:11:09.975 --> 01:11:12.645
- BECCA: Go. go. go. Hurry.
- TYLER: Brought a coat. I'm coming.

1083
01:11:14.313 --> 01:11:15.689
Okay. open it.

1084
01:11:16.482 --> 01:11:18.734
BECCA: (GASPS) What is that?

1085
01:11:18.859 --> 01:11:19.885
(GASPS)

1086
01:11:19.985 --> 01:11:23.155
Picked teams. It's young versus old.

1087
01:11:37.169 --> 01:11:40.714
POP POP: Stop rolling all
the dice on every roll!

1088
01:11:40.881 --> 01:11:42.116
You're losing the game for us!

1089
01:11:42.216 --> 01:11:43.409
NANA: No. I'm not.

1090
01:11:43.509 --> 01:11:44.827
(CHUCKLING) We don't have to keep score.

1091
01:11:44.927 --> 01:11:46.829
I'm a <i>Yahtzee</i> master.

1092
01:11:46.929 --> 01:11:50.124
Doesn't everyone in the cafeteria
call me the <i>Yahtzee</i> master?

1093
01:11:50.224 --> 01:11:51.250
(MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO)

1094
01:11:51.350 --> 01:11:53.310
What cafeteria?

1095
01:11:53.727 --> 01:11:55.421
You wanna win at <i>Yahtzee.</i> listen to me.

1096
01:11:55.521 --> 01:11:58.649
You're not a <i>Yahtzee</i> master.
That takes 10 years.

1097
01:12:04.154 --> 01:12:08.575
See? He's using strategy!
A Milton Bradley-approved strategy.

1098
01:12:08.701 --> 01:12:09.994
I don't know what I'm doing.

1099
01:12:10.744 --> 01:12:13.314
This game is made by Hasbro. Pop Pop.

1100
01:12:13.414 --> 01:12:14.832
That's a lie.

1101
01:12:14.957 --> 01:12:16.901
It used to be made by Milton Bradley.

1102
01:12:17.001 --> 01:12:19.111
Who cares. Becca?

1103
01:12:19.211 --> 01:12:20.921
Finally!

1104
01:12:21.046 --> 01:12:22.881
- I'm having so much fun.
- (LAUGHS)

1105
01:12:26.093 --> 01:12:27.870
- (CHUCKLES)
- (SIGHS)

1106
01:12:27.970 --> 01:12:31.348
Wow. my battery's running low.
I'll be right back.

1107
01:12:33.767 --> 01:12:35.519
You keep playing with them. T.

1108
01:12:36.520 --> 01:12:38.147
Just keep playing.

1109
01:12:38.439 --> 01:12:39.565
I'll be right back.

1110
01:12:40.607 --> 01:12:41.984
(SPITS)

1111
01:12:54.872 --> 01:12:56.415
(GRUMBLING)

1112
01:13:05.632 --> 01:13:07.551
(MUNCHING)

1113
01:13:13.640 --> 01:13:15.142
Becca?

1114
01:13:21.231 --> 01:13:22.983
(WHISPERS) Katy Perry.

1115
01:13:26.403 --> 01:13:28.197
What time is it. Nana?

1116
01:13:28.864 --> 01:13:30.657
Isn't it getting late?

1117
01:13:35.579 --> 01:13:37.106
(SCREAMING) Yahtzee!

1118
01:13:37.206 --> 01:13:38.248
(YELLS) Becca!

1119
01:13:39.583 --> 01:13:41.627
(BECCA BREATHING HEAVILY)

1120
01:13:43.170 --> 01:13:45.380
I'm going down into the basement.

1121
01:13:49.176 --> 01:13:51.845
I think they have my grandparents here.

1122
01:13:52.513 --> 01:13:54.640
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1123
01:14:00.020 --> 01:14:01.355
Pop Pop?

1124
01:14:02.106 --> 01:14:04.858
Nana? Are you down here?

1125
01:14:15.786 --> 01:14:18.038
Things are not working out tonight.

1126
01:14:27.297 --> 01:14:29.049
It's half past nine.

1127
01:14:37.558 --> 01:14:40.269
I have to get your Nana to her room.
You wait here.

1128
01:14:48.902 --> 01:14:50.904
(BECCA BREATHING HEAVILY)

1129
01:14:53.824 --> 01:14:55.075
BECCA: (WHISPERING) Nana?

1130
01:14:56.160 --> 01:14:57.244
Pop Pop?

1131
01:15:15.137 --> 01:15:17.581
"Maple Shade Psychiatric Hospital"?

1132
01:15:17.681 --> 01:15:18.765
(GASPS)

1133
01:15:23.937 --> 01:15:27.191
Should the three of us finish the game?

1134
01:15:34.448 --> 01:15:36.408
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1135
01:15:39.620 --> 01:15:40.787
(WHIMPERS)

1136
01:15:40.913 --> 01:15:41.897
(GASPS)

1137
01:15:41.997 --> 01:15:43.373
(YELLS)

1138
01:15:43.707 --> 01:15:46.710
My name is Becca Jamison.
If you find this footage...

1139
01:15:46.835 --> 01:15:48.545
- (SCREAMS)
- My name is Mitchel.

1140
01:15:50.339 --> 01:15:53.008
They kept telling us you were so great.

1141
01:15:53.133 --> 01:15:55.702
How you're gonna visit.
how you're gonna be a family.

1142
01:15:55.802 --> 01:15:57.913
That was a bad thing they did.

1143
01:15:58.013 --> 01:16:00.541
They knew Claire
had put her two children

1144
01:16:00.641 --> 01:16:02.684
in those suitcases in the pond.

1145
01:16:03.727 --> 01:16:07.131
She deserved this week as a grandma.

1146
01:16:07.231 --> 01:16:10.150
Claire's kids are on Sinmorfitellia.

1147
01:16:11.693 --> 01:16:13.320
You're gonna join them!

1148
01:16:13.862 --> 01:16:15.347
- (BECCA SCREAMS)
- (POP POP GRUNTS)

1149
01:16:15.447 --> 01:16:17.057
- (BECCA YELLS)
- (POP POP GRUNTS)

1150
01:16:17.157 --> 01:16:18.659
(SCREAMS)

1151
01:16:18.992 --> 01:16:19.993
BECCA: Stop!

1152
01:16:22.746 --> 01:16:27.484
POP POP: The only way to Sinmorfitellia
from here is through the well.

1153
01:16:27.584 --> 01:16:28.777
BECCA: Stop!

1154
01:16:28.877 --> 01:16:30.003
(SIGHS)

1155
01:16:30.420 --> 01:16:33.240
- Wasn't it a perfect week?
- (WHIMPERS)

1156
01:16:33.340 --> 01:16:35.550
I promised her it would be.

1157
01:16:37.928 --> 01:16:40.514
The white thing with
yellow eyes is real.

1158
01:16:41.682 --> 01:16:44.685
It waits for us.
I saw it out in the field.

1159
01:16:46.270 --> 01:16:48.021
It was laughing at us. (GRUNTS)

1160
01:16:48.355 --> 01:16:49.481
(GROANS)

1161
01:16:51.525 --> 01:16:53.568
(GRUNTS)

1162
01:16:54.903 --> 01:16:56.363
BECCA: They're murderers. Tyler!

1163
01:16:56.530 --> 01:16:57.739
Becca!

1164
01:16:57.864 --> 01:16:59.950
- Get out of here. dummy! Run!
- (GROANS)

1165
01:17:03.036 --> 01:17:04.371
TYLER: Becca!

1166
01:17:05.205 --> 01:17:06.873
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1167
01:17:09.042 --> 01:17:11.044
POP POP: We're all dying today. Becca.

1168
01:17:11.211 --> 01:17:12.587
- BECCA: No...
- (DOOR BANGS)

1169
01:17:15.507 --> 01:17:17.134
(BECCA GRUNTING)

1170
01:17:18.552 --> 01:17:20.721
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1171
01:17:22.723 --> 01:17:24.558
(WHIMPERING)

1172
01:17:24.725 --> 01:17:26.101
(GROANS)

1173
01:17:26.560 --> 01:17:28.603
(BREATHES RAGGEDLY)

1174
01:17:33.567 --> 01:17:34.818
(SCREAMS)

1175
01:17:46.663 --> 01:17:50.500
You have a magic spell on you.

1176
01:17:57.215 --> 01:17:58.967
(WHIMPERING)

1177
01:18:09.227 --> 01:18:10.228
(WATER RUNNING)

1178
01:18:39.341 --> 01:18:40.675
(YELLING) Help!

1179
01:18:40.801 --> 01:18:41.952
Help!

1180
01:18:42.052 --> 01:18:43.303
(GRUNTS)

1181
01:18:44.846 --> 01:18:46.681
(SHUDDERING)

1182
01:19:02.155 --> 01:19:04.199
POP POP: (WHISPERS) I never liked you.

1183
01:19:04.991 --> 01:19:05.992
(TYLER WHIMPERS)

1184
01:19:06.201 --> 01:19:08.245
(NANA MOANING)

1185
01:19:08.620 --> 01:19:10.080
BECCA: Claire?

1186
01:19:11.998 --> 01:19:13.792
I'll tell you a story.

1187
01:19:18.922 --> 01:19:21.508
(BECCA BREATHING HEAVILY)

1188
01:19:27.764 --> 01:19:29.057
(GASPS)

1189
01:19:41.528 --> 01:19:43.196
(CLATTERING)

1190
01:19:44.656 --> 01:19:46.116
(YELPS)

1191
01:19:54.875 --> 01:19:58.170
I have to go to the train
to go to the costume party.

1192
01:19:58.295 --> 01:20:00.088
It's a company party.

1193
01:20:02.215 --> 01:20:04.217
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1194
01:20:09.514 --> 01:20:10.724
(GASPS)

1195
01:20:14.352 --> 01:20:16.062
That's not now.

1196
01:20:17.856 --> 01:20:19.274
I know that!

1197
01:20:28.909 --> 01:20:30.869
- (NANA GIGGLES)
- (BECCA YELPS)

1198
01:20:33.246 --> 01:20:35.415
(SNARLS)

1199
01:20:37.417 --> 01:20:39.544
- (GROWLS)
- (WHIMPERS)

1200
01:20:46.968 --> 01:20:48.929
(TYLER WHIMPERING)

1201
01:20:53.183 --> 01:20:55.936
- You have a problem with germs. don't you?
- (WHIMPERS)

1202
01:21:03.610 --> 01:21:05.612
- (BECCA WHIMPERS)
- (NANA LAUGHS)

1203
01:21:17.791 --> 01:21:19.668
(SNARLING LOUDLY)

1204
01:21:35.016 --> 01:21:36.142
(SNIFFS)

1205
01:21:38.311 --> 01:21:40.355
- (GROWLS)
- (SCREAMS)

1206
01:21:40.522 --> 01:21:42.148
(GRUNTING)

1207
01:21:42.983 --> 01:21:44.234
NANA: I don't like you.

1208
01:21:44.609 --> 01:21:46.486
(BECCA GRUNTING)

1209
01:21:48.238 --> 01:21:49.656
(SCREAMING)

1210
01:21:51.324 --> 01:21:52.826
(GROWLING)

1211
01:21:56.830 --> 01:21:58.498
(BECCA GROANING)

1212
01:22:03.420 --> 01:22:05.463
(SCREAMS. CHOKING)

1213
01:22:08.383 --> 01:22:09.634
(RETCHES)

1214
01:22:16.683 --> 01:22:18.852
(SCREAMING)

1215
01:22:20.020 --> 01:22:23.398
You are blind. You are blind.

1216
01:22:24.399 --> 01:22:28.236
I am the exposer. I am a seer.

1217
01:22:28.361 --> 01:22:32.907
I see the veiny...

1218
01:22:33.867 --> 01:22:35.577
...deformed...

1219
01:22:36.870 --> 01:22:38.747
...face of the world.

1220
01:22:44.711 --> 01:22:46.796
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

1221
01:22:47.380 --> 01:22:49.883
(GRUNTING)

1222
01:22:55.680 --> 01:22:57.223
(KNOB CLATTERS)

1223
01:23:02.187 --> 01:23:04.731
- We can all be saved tonight.
- (SHUDDERING)

1224
01:23:05.857 --> 01:23:09.194
Your magic spell will be lifted.

1225
01:23:10.570 --> 01:23:11.780
(BECCA SCREAMS)

1226
01:23:12.238 --> 01:23:14.741
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1227
01:23:20.288 --> 01:23:21.956
- Becca!
- (BECCA YELPS)

1228
01:23:24.918 --> 01:23:27.253
Have you been watching me?

1229
01:23:27.379 --> 01:23:30.048
BECCA: (SOBBING) Run. Tyler. run!

1230
01:23:30.548 --> 01:23:32.509
- (TYLER GROANS)
- (POP POP GRUNTS)

1231
01:23:33.718 --> 01:23:35.261
Eyes on the runner!

1232
01:23:35.387 --> 01:23:38.473
Watch his hips! Watch his hips!

1233
01:23:38.932 --> 01:23:41.101
(SCREAMING)

1234
01:23:42.769 --> 01:23:43.878
Stay low!

1235
01:23:43.978 --> 01:23:46.481
Wrap the arms! Wrap the arms!

1236
01:23:46.648 --> 01:23:47.732
BECCA: (SOBBING) Tyler?

1237
01:23:49.984 --> 01:23:52.445
(GROANING ANGRILY)

1238
01:23:54.864 --> 01:23:55.974
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

